SEARCHING:

f{char} - search forward

F{char} - search backwards

t{char} - search BEFORE the char

T{char} - search AFTER the char

; - repeats the search in the same direction that it was started

, - repeats it backward

/{word} - search for the word (n - next, N - back)



TRANSFORM:

:s/old/new/g - change the searched word of the entire LINE from the old word to the new word.

:%s/old/new/g - change the searched word of the entire FILE from the old word to the new word.
